63.4	Fargo_(film)	Fargo (film)	Fargo is a 1996 American dark comedy-crime film produced, directed and written by brothers Joel and Ethan Coen. It stars Frances McDormand as a pregnant police chief who investigates a series of homicides, William H. Macy as a car salesman who hires two criminals to kidnap his wife, Steve Buscemi and Peter Stormare as the criminals, and Harve Presnell as the salesman's father-in-law.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/ac/Fargo.jpg/220px-Fargo.jpg
